                            <comment id="12878463" author="drew.farris" created="Mon, 14 Jun 2010 04:28:42 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a start: the Lucene TokenFilter implementation that takes a o.a.hadoop.util.bloom.Filter (BloomFilter) class and optionally keeps or tosses tokens that are members of the filter.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I doubt the package name is appropriate or even if something like this belongs in mahout, but I didn&apos;t spot it elsewhere.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12878465" author="jake.mannix" created="Mon, 14 Jun 2010 04:46:00 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Awesome, you rock, Drew!   Very cool.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13037116" author="tdunning" created="Fri, 20 May 2011 23:18:34 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a very nice capability and given that it is done by Drew, it is likely good code.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Should we commit this or pass it over to Lucene?&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13037131" author="drew.farris" created="Fri, 20 May 2011 23:29:10 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the good words Ted.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At quick glance there are some rough edges that need to be cleaned up here. I&apos;ll try to take a pass at it this weekend.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13044278" author="srowen" created="Sat, 4 Jun 2011 12:14:21 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Drew I touched this up a little and committed it. It uses some deprecated APIs (deprecated in Lucene 3.x?) so may want to have a second look at it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13044334" author="hudson" created="Sat, 4 Jun 2011 18:07:58 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Mahout-Quality #858 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/hudson/job/Mahout-Quality/858/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/hudson/job/Mahout-Quality/858/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
